  "content": "# Session Record — 2026-03-19 (Full Day)\n\n## Final State\n- Build: 0 warnings, 0 clippy warnings\n- Tests: 0 failures (24 suites, 625+ tests)\n- Both repos pushed to master\n\n## Major Deliverables\n1. Dashboard traces fixed (was all zeros → real trace trees with timing)\n2. `corvia bench run/report/compare` CLI commands (M6 product feature)\n3. Dashboard embedded in binary via rust-embed\n4. Config-driven RAG retriever/augmenter selection\n5. 69 eval queries with NDCG@10, Precision@K metrics\n6. Graph expansion A/B test (vector wins 0.773 vs 0.734, 34x faster)\n7. Architecture challenge — 10 decisions reviewed\n8. Zero-warning build (bollard migration, clippy, MSRV 1.91)\n9. 13 dashboard handler tests\n10. JSON embedding exclusion (~80% disk savings)\n11. Knowledge health tracking via reasoner (3697 orphaned nodes investigated)\n12. 5 new embedding models (Snowflake Arctic, GTE)\n13. Agent auto-registration via REST\n14. Comprehensive LLMOps benchmarking research\n\n## Chat Model Status\n- Qwen3-1.7B Q4_K_M runs on CPU at ~43s/query\n- Faithfulness: 0.630, Answer Relevance: 0.667\n- GPU CUDA blocked: nvcc 12.8 incompatible with Debian trixie glibc 2.40+\n- Resolution: CUDA 12.9+ or Ubuntu base image\n\n## Process Established\n- Deep 3-persona independent subagent reviews (SWE/PM/QA)\n- Pre-implementation review gate\n- Setback recovery protocol\n- All findings persisted to corvia knowledge base\n\n## Eval Baselines\n- Retrieval: NDCG@10=0.656, Precision@5=49.6%, MRR=0.608\n- Generation: Faithfulness=0.630, Relevance=0.667 (CPU, 3/5 queries)\n- Graph A/B: vector 0.773 vs graph 0.734 relevance, 57ms vs 1958ms",
